title: Acting SFH on delay in handling baby dead body
content_text:
p>
    Following is the transcript of remarks (English portion) made by the Acting 
    Secretary for Food and Health, Professor Gabriel Leung, on an incident at 
    the mortuary of Princess Margaret Hospital involving delay in handling the 
    dead body of a baby, at a media session after attending a public function 
    today (October 23): Reporter: ...... (About the incident) Acting Secretary for Food and Health: When I learnt about this incident last 
    night, I felt shocked and saddened. Saddened that a similar incident has

night, I felt shocked and saddened. Saddened that a similar incident has 
    happened again, but most of all saddened for the family who have already 
    lost a child in the process. Please allow me this opportunity to apologise 
    and send my deepest condolences to the family once again. I have already 
    asked the Hospital Authority to thoroughly investigate the incident and 
    report back with a detailed submission within two weeks. Given all the 
    improvement measures, both in terms of hardware as well as software 
    including more detailed guidance to frontline colleagues, this incident has

including more detailed guidance to frontline colleagues, this incident has 
    happened. I think it really deserves close scrutiny including the 
    environment and culture of our hospital mortuary at Princess Margaret 
    Hospital. Reporter: ...... (About the penalty) Acting Secretary for Food and Health: I think it will be premature and 
    inappropriate for me to speculate on the specific details of the case before 
    the completion of the report. So I would like to ask for your indulgence and 
    allow the space and the two-week time period for the Hospital Authority and

allow the space and the two-week time period for the Hospital Authority and Princess Margaret Hospital to come up with the complete report before we make any decision forward. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
